	vector diagrams (

<link id="a1035" url="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c8plj9UsJbg">

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c8plj9UsJbg

</link>

).

</item>


	

<item id="li1036">
An understanding of the use of a protractor for measuring angles (

<link id="a1036" url="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v-F06HgiUpw">

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v-F06HgiUpw

</link>

).

</item>


	

<item id="li1037">
A basic understanding of the use of sine, cosine, and tangent from 
	trigonometry (

<link id="a1037" url="http://www.clarku.edu/~djoyce/trig/">

http://www.clarku.edu/~djoyce/trig/

</link>

